A Nigerian lady identified as Cynthia Anyisia has taken to social media  to advise Nigerian men on the kind of women to marry. Daily Times Nigeria gathered that she advised men to marry women who can at least afford to pay electricity bill in their absence. READ ALSO: Starting a new relationship? According to her, Nigerian men when thinking of marriage, should lookout for that lady who can afford to “at least” pay NEPA bills in their absence, unlike those who would let power supply to be disconnected and wait for the husband to return so they could tell him “honey they have cut our light”. She wrote in a popular Facebook group, “Marry a woman that can at least pay for Nepa bills. Not the one that will say honey they have cut our light”.